00:01:43.302 --> 00:01:45.710 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: How did you get
involved in your interest

00:01:45.710 --> 00:01:47.123 align:middle line:90%
in ancient civilizations?

00:01:47.123 --> 00:01:49.040 align:middle line:84%
>>LACROIX: Well, it
certainly wasn't something

00:01:49.040 --> 00:01:50.270 align:middle line:90%
that I had planned for.

00:01:50.270 --> 00:01:51.900 align:middle line:84%
I was just a very
inquisitive person.

00:01:51.900 --> 00:01:55.430 align:middle line:84%
And I remember just going
along the inquisitive road

00:01:55.430 --> 00:01:58.440 align:middle line:84%
of being curious about so
many things in the world.

00:01:58.440 --> 00:02:00.050 align:middle line:84%
And when I started
to really look

00:02:00.050 --> 00:02:03.290 align:middle line:84%
into some of these
researchers, like

00:02:03.290 --> 00:02:05.180 align:middle line:84%
Graham Hancock and
Randall Carlson

00:02:05.180 --> 00:02:07.370 align:middle line:84%
and Robert Bauval
and Robert Schoch.

00:02:07.370 --> 00:02:09.889 align:middle line:84%
You start to see
some of the research

00:02:09.889 --> 00:02:11.630 align:middle line:84%
that they're
providing, which really

00:02:11.630 --> 00:02:12.950 align:middle line:90%
challenges the narrative.

00:02:12.950 --> 00:02:16.880 align:middle line:84%
And instead of being
something that, perhaps,

00:02:16.880 --> 00:02:18.680 align:middle line:84%
makes you less
interested in history,

00:02:18.680 --> 00:02:20.690 align:middle line:84%
it excites you more
because of, really,

00:02:20.690 --> 00:02:22.610 align:middle line:84%
this hidden truth,
you could call it,

00:02:22.610 --> 00:02:25.250 align:middle line:84%
that seems to exist that
is not being recognized.

00:02:25.250 --> 00:02:27.110 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: In "Ancient
Civilizations"

00:02:27.110 --> 00:02:29.610 align:middle line:90%
what is your approach?

00:02:29.610 --> 00:02:32.210 align:middle line:84%
>>LACROIX: Our approach
now, we are completely

00:02:32.210 --> 00:02:36.170 align:middle line:84%
revitalizing and rechanging
"Ancient Civilizations"

00:02:36.170 --> 00:02:38.570 align:middle line:84%
into a show that is
going to be the finest

00:02:38.570 --> 00:02:42.320 align:middle line:84%
example of an evidence-driven
show with a high production

00:02:42.320 --> 00:02:44.780 align:middle line:84%
value and a lot of
very important speakers

00:02:44.780 --> 00:02:47.870 align:middle line:84%
that then looks at these
topics with the most

00:02:47.870 --> 00:02:49.730 align:middle line:84%
amount of evidence
possible around the world

00:02:49.730 --> 00:02:52.310 align:middle line:84%
to try to recreate
this lost story,

00:02:52.310 --> 00:02:55.440 align:middle line:84%
recreate our story from
how far back it goes

00:02:55.440 --> 00:02:58.430 align:middle line:84%
and how sophisticated it is
but bring it to this level

00:02:58.430 --> 00:03:01.370 align:middle line:84%
where it's from a
scholarly academic level.

00:03:01.370 --> 00:03:03.110 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: How far
back does it go?

00:03:03.110 --> 00:03:04.190 align:middle line:84%
>>LACROIX: Well, that's
a difficult question

00:03:04.190 --> 00:03:06.170 align:middle line:84%
to answer because
we're really looking

00:03:06.170 --> 00:03:08.150 align:middle line:84%
at the evidence from
the ancient Sumerians

00:03:08.150 --> 00:03:11.480 align:middle line:84%
or looking at the
ancient Egyptian cultures

00:03:11.480 --> 00:03:13.130 align:middle line:90%
or the ancient Hindu cultures.

00:03:13.130 --> 00:03:16.640 align:middle line:84%
Really, we have a story that
at least goes back 20, perhaps,

00:03:16.640 --> 00:03:18.350 align:middle line:90%
over 50,000 years ago.

00:03:18.350 --> 00:03:19.550 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: Wow.

00:03:19.550 --> 00:03:20.390 align:middle line:84%
>>LACROIX: And we're
not talking about--

00:03:20.390 --> 00:03:20.870 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: That far back?

00:03:20.870 --> 00:03:22.460 align:middle line:84%
>>LACROIX: Well, we're not
talking about nomadic hunter

00:03:22.460 --> 00:03:23.260 align:middle line:90%
gatherers.

00:03:23.260 --> 00:03:26.480 align:middle line:84%
We're talking about when
civilization emerged.

00:03:26.480 --> 00:03:28.213 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: Sophisticated
civilizations.

00:03:28.213 --> 00:03:29.630 align:middle line:84%
>>LACROIX: Yeah,
exactly, exactly.

00:03:29.630 --> 00:03:31.880 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: Which is phenomenal.

00:03:31.880 --> 00:03:35.600 align:middle line:84%
What kind of technology do you
think they had that far back?

00:03:35.600 --> 00:03:38.330 align:middle line:84%
>>LACROIX: Well, it may not
be necessarily a question

00:03:38.330 --> 00:03:40.910 align:middle line:84%
of the types of technology
because it may be more

00:03:40.910 --> 00:03:43.070 align:middle line:84%
about a deep
understanding of nature

00:03:43.070 --> 00:03:45.458 align:middle line:84%
and about the laws of
physics and reality

00:03:45.458 --> 00:03:47.750 align:middle line:84%
because, when we look at some
of these great structures

00:03:47.750 --> 00:03:49.640 align:middle line:84%
like the Great Pyramid
of Giza, 2 and 1/2

00:03:49.640 --> 00:03:53.690 align:middle line:84%
million megalithic blocks, an
average of 10 to 15 tons each,

00:03:53.690 --> 00:03:56.000 align:middle line:84%
we look at that,
and if you actually

00:03:56.000 --> 00:03:57.950 align:middle line:84%
try to consider how
if they were to lay

00:03:57.950 --> 00:04:01.190 align:middle line:84%
each block with sheer
manpower, to try

00:04:01.190 --> 00:04:04.200 align:middle line:84%
to do that over the course of
the time period we're given,

00:04:04.200 --> 00:04:05.622 align:middle line:90%
it seems completely impossible.

00:04:05.622 --> 00:04:07.580 align:middle line:84%
And when we look at other
megalithic structures

00:04:07.580 --> 00:04:10.205 align:middle line:84%
around the world, it seems that
there's something else going on

00:04:10.205 --> 00:04:12.680 align:middle line:84%
besides technology, maybe
more of an understanding

00:04:12.680 --> 00:04:16.760 align:middle line:84%
of harmonics and
frequency related to some

00:04:16.760 --> 00:04:18.079 align:middle line:90%
of these ancient structures.

00:04:18.079 --> 00:04:19.621 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: What are
some of the things

00:04:19.621 --> 00:04:22.320 align:middle line:84%
you get involved with in the
new season in terms of topics?

00:04:22.320 --> 00:04:24.350 align:middle line:84%
>>LACROIX: One of the
big directional changes

00:04:24.350 --> 00:04:27.800 align:middle line:84%
of "Ancient Civilizations" that
we've done going from seasons 1

00:04:27.800 --> 00:04:31.160 align:middle line:84%
through 3, going into season
4 now and then into season 5

00:04:31.160 --> 00:04:34.520 align:middle line:84%
and beyond is now, instead of
looking at concepts and core

00:04:34.520 --> 00:04:37.310 align:middle line:84%
ideas from around the
world about civilizations,

00:04:37.310 --> 00:04:39.770 align:middle line:84%
we're actually focusing
on specific civilizations.

00:04:39.770 --> 00:04:41.480 align:middle line:84%
So for instance,
looking at, well,

00:04:41.480 --> 00:04:44.270 align:middle line:84%
when did the first original
Egyptian civilizations

00:04:44.270 --> 00:04:46.370 align:middle line:84%
that built the
pyramids, when did they

00:04:46.370 --> 00:04:47.870 align:middle line:90%
come around in history?

00:04:47.870 --> 00:04:49.752 align:middle line:84%
And when did they get
their start, and how

00:04:49.752 --> 00:04:50.960 align:middle line:90%
did they get their knowledge?

00:04:50.960 --> 00:04:53.570 align:middle line:84%
And then looking at
places like Easter Island

00:04:53.570 --> 00:04:56.930 align:middle line:84%
with the ancient Moai heads and
how far down under the ground

00:04:56.930 --> 00:04:59.540 align:middle line:84%
they go and how they're part
of a civilization that greatly

00:04:59.540 --> 00:05:02.698 align:middle line:84%
predates the Rapa Nui, all
the way to places like Japan,

00:05:02.698 --> 00:05:04.490 align:middle line:84%
which really hasn't
been talked about a lot

00:05:04.490 --> 00:05:07.820 align:middle line:84%
with their megaliths, and
Machu Picchu, and Tiwanaku,

00:05:07.820 --> 00:05:10.430 align:middle line:84%
and the underwater cities
like Dwarka, India.

00:05:10.430 --> 00:05:13.220 align:middle line:84%
We're really taking this
to a new direction where

00:05:13.220 --> 00:05:15.950 align:middle line:84%
we're specifically looking
at civilizations that

00:05:15.950 --> 00:05:18.960 align:middle line:84%
existed before the Younger
Dryas catastrophes of 12,000

00:05:18.960 --> 00:05:19.760 align:middle line:90%
years ago.

00:05:19.760 --> 00:05:21.020 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: That's exciting.

00:05:21.020 --> 00:05:24.270 align:middle line:84%
Do you get into the how
were the pyramids built?

00:05:24.270 --> 00:05:25.070 align:middle line:90%
>>LACROIX: We do.

00:05:25.070 --> 00:05:28.910 align:middle line:84%
We talk a lot about some of the
knowledge and some of the ways

00:05:28.910 --> 00:05:31.790 align:middle line:84%
in which those structures
were put together and really

00:05:31.790 --> 00:05:35.300 align:middle line:84%
go into, well, how old are they,
if we look at star alignments

00:05:35.300 --> 00:05:37.550 align:middle line:84%
and considering the
procession of the equinox?

00:05:37.550 --> 00:05:40.850 align:middle line:84%
We have to try to consider that
these dates that we're told

00:05:40.850 --> 00:05:43.280 align:middle line:84%
and this time frame
is completely wrong.

00:05:43.280 --> 00:05:45.050 align:middle line:84%
And we have to
start over and try

00:05:45.050 --> 00:05:48.100 align:middle line:84%
to listen to what the
evidence says to recreate

00:05:48.100 --> 00:05:50.020 align:middle line:90%
the story of our story.

00:05:50.020 --> 00:05:53.170 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: There was a chap by
the name of Edward Leedskalnin,

00:05:53.170 --> 00:05:57.730 align:middle line:84%
who was from Latvia, who
came to the United States

00:05:57.730 --> 00:06:01.000 align:middle line:84%
and built something that
still mystifies everybody.

00:06:01.000 --> 00:06:02.330 align:middle line:90%
We call it Coral Castle.

00:06:02.330 --> 00:06:03.130 align:middle line:90%
>>LACROIX: Yep.

00:06:03.130 --> 00:06:09.370 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: This frail man, small,
moved blocks almost the size

00:06:09.370 --> 00:06:12.670 align:middle line:84%
of the pyramids to
build Coral Castle.

00:06:12.670 --> 00:06:14.510 align:middle line:90%
How in the world did he do that?

00:06:14.510 --> 00:06:15.860 align:middle line:90%
And you look at him, don't you?

00:06:15.860 --> 00:06:17.860 align:middle line:84%
>>LACROIX: It's an
interesting story, and people

00:06:17.860 --> 00:06:21.280 align:middle line:84%
that describe catching him
in the middle of his building

00:06:21.280 --> 00:06:23.290 align:middle line:84%
state, that he did
it all alone, and he

00:06:23.290 --> 00:06:25.990 align:middle line:84%
would do it when no one
was around, often at night.

00:06:25.990 --> 00:06:30.580 align:middle line:84%
And somehow, he would
take these massive blocks

00:06:30.580 --> 00:06:32.740 align:middle line:84%
and he would build them
up to create Coral Castle.

00:06:32.740 --> 00:06:33.740 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: And move them.

00:06:33.740 --> 00:06:35.410 align:middle line:84%
>>LACROIX: But he
states that he learned

00:06:35.410 --> 00:06:38.020 align:middle line:84%
the secrets of the
pyramid builders of Giza,

00:06:38.020 --> 00:06:40.900 align:middle line:84%
and essentially, he
understood the same things

00:06:40.900 --> 00:06:42.580 align:middle line:84%
that they did, which
I think gets back

00:06:42.580 --> 00:06:46.180 align:middle line:84%
into looking at the type of
work that Nikola Tesla did.

00:06:46.180 --> 00:06:48.790 align:middle line:84%
We're looking at sound and
frequency and vibration.

00:06:48.790 --> 00:06:49.930 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: And magnetism.

00:06:49.930 --> 00:06:52.180 align:middle line:84%
>>LACROIX: Right, that
seems to be the core of this

00:06:52.180 --> 00:06:53.500 align:middle line:90%
rather than sheer manpower.

00:06:53.500 --> 00:06:56.140 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: He was a staunch
believer in magnetism,

00:06:56.140 --> 00:06:57.710 align:middle line:90%
even wrote a small book on that.

00:06:57.710 --> 00:06:58.810 align:middle line:90%
>>LACROIX: Yeah, exactly.

00:06:58.810 --> 00:07:03.310 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: I wonder if he
somehow magnetized the blocks

00:07:03.310 --> 00:07:06.762 align:middle line:84%
and repelled them and just
floated them into place.

00:07:06.762 --> 00:07:08.470 align:middle line:84%
>>LACROIX: Well, that's
one of the things

00:07:08.470 --> 00:07:11.560 align:middle line:84%
that it comes into place
because, if our planet is based

00:07:11.560 --> 00:07:15.160 align:middle line:84%
on this electromagnetism of the
entire North and South Pole,

00:07:15.160 --> 00:07:17.350 align:middle line:84%
with these energy
centers, if you knew,

00:07:17.350 --> 00:07:19.430 align:middle line:84%
just like Nikola
Tesla talked about,

00:07:19.430 --> 00:07:22.390 align:middle line:84%
if you knew how to tap into that
free energy and understanding

00:07:22.390 --> 00:07:24.760 align:middle line:84%
magnetism, you can
essentially do things that we

00:07:24.760 --> 00:07:26.200 align:middle line:90%
think are impossible today.

00:07:26.200 --> 00:07:28.242 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: Well, Matt,
we've teased people enough.

00:07:28.242 --> 00:07:30.130 align:middle line:84%
Let's show them a little
glimpse of season 4

00:07:30.130 --> 00:07:31.540 align:middle line:90%
