been done in Greenland

00:10:24.830 --> 00:10:26.882 align:middle line:84%
and Antarctica,
really try to recreate

00:10:26.882 --> 00:10:28.340 align:middle line:84%
what the atmosphere
and the climate

00:10:28.340 --> 00:10:31.280 align:middle line:84%
was like back then to
try to understand, well,

00:10:31.280 --> 00:10:34.100 align:middle line:84%
if a disaster did occur,
what is the science

00:10:34.100 --> 00:10:38.660 align:middle line:84%
that that's based on to try
to understand, well, how does

00:10:38.660 --> 00:10:40.130 align:middle line:90%
all this fit into our story?

00:10:40.130 --> 00:10:42.335 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: What are
prediluvian civilizations?

00:10:42.335 --> 00:10:44.710 align:middle line:84%
>>LACROIX: That's a really
important thing to understand.

00:10:44.710 --> 00:10:46.940 align:middle line:84%
There's other terms
that have been used.

00:10:46.940 --> 00:10:49.970 align:middle line:84%
They essentially mean the
same thing, antediluvian,

00:10:49.970 --> 00:10:51.860 align:middle line:90%
prediluvian, preflood.

00:10:51.860 --> 00:10:53.990 align:middle line:84%
Essentially, that
time period has

00:10:53.990 --> 00:10:56.900 align:middle line:84%
been identified geologically
and through climatology

00:10:56.900 --> 00:11:00.050 align:middle line:84%
as being before these
events of the Younger Dryas.

00:11:00.050 --> 00:11:02.840 align:middle line:84%
The Younger Dryas is
called that because it's

00:11:02.840 --> 00:11:05.450 align:middle line:84%
a very disruptive time
period in history that

00:11:05.450 --> 00:11:10.340 align:middle line:84%
came between around 10,800
years ago and 13,000 years ago.

00:11:10.340 --> 00:11:13.430 align:middle line:84%
And it's this time period
of several thousand years

00:11:13.430 --> 00:11:17.420 align:middle line:84%
that essentially has these
incredibly disastrous events

00:11:17.420 --> 00:11:18.680 align:middle line:90%
that occurred on the Earth.

00:11:18.680 --> 00:11:20.900 align:middle line:84%
And that's what we
think of as the flood

00:11:20.900 --> 00:11:23.720 align:middle line:84%
because, ultimately, the
totality of those events--

00:11:23.720 --> 00:11:24.020 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: The Noah flood.

00:11:24.020 --> 00:11:24.590 align:middle line:90%
The Noah flood?

00:11:24.590 --> 00:11:26.757 align:middle line:84%
>>LACROIX: Exactly, ultimately,
the totality of that

00:11:26.757 --> 00:11:28.250 align:middle line:84%
was that there was
a massive flood.

00:11:28.250 --> 00:11:31.700 align:middle line:84%
I think that was mostly
based on tsunamis worldwide.

00:11:31.700 --> 00:11:34.760 align:middle line:84%
But either way, what that
means is prediluvian or any

00:11:34.760 --> 00:11:38.990 align:middle line:84%
of the civilizations that
existed before that event.

00:11:38.990 --> 00:11:42.200 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: There's no question
that the Bible has spelled out

00:11:42.200 --> 00:11:44.990 align:middle line:84%
a lot of strange things that
happened on this planet.

00:11:44.990 --> 00:11:48.500 align:middle line:84%
But as you have pointed out,
there's no other history.

00:11:48.500 --> 00:11:50.870 align:middle line:84%
There's no other
record of things

00:11:50.870 --> 00:11:53.270 align:middle line:84%
that we had where the
knowledge is lost.

00:11:53.270 --> 00:11:56.390 align:middle line:84%
What happened to the
plans for the pyramids?

00:11:56.390 --> 00:11:58.490 align:middle line:84%
Surely they had to
be able to construct

00:11:58.490 --> 00:12:01.970 align:middle line:84%
them architecturally with
sketches or something

00:12:01.970 --> 00:12:03.470 align:middle line:90%
on papyrus.

00:12:03.470 --> 00:12:04.462 align:middle line:90%
Where are they?

00:12:04.462 --> 00:12:06.920 align:middle line:84%
>>LACROIX: Well, that's actually
a very good point to make.

00:12:06.920 --> 00:12:10.550 align:middle line:84%
When we look at papyrus and
we look at paper records, what

00:12:10.550 --> 00:12:13.280 align:middle line:84%
we find is that paper
specifically can only

00:12:13.280 --> 00:12:15.425 align:middle line:90%
last 500 to 1,000 years.

00:12:15.425 --> 00:12:16.550 align:middle line:90%
And when we look at these--

00:12:16.550 --> 00:12:16.940 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: And then
it disintegrates.

00:12:16.940 --> 00:12:18.023 align:middle line:90%
>>LACROIX: Right, exactly.

00:12:18.023 --> 00:12:20.180 align:middle line:84%
So how do you have a
message be protected

00:12:20.180 --> 00:12:21.590 align:middle line:90%
that can actually survive?

00:12:21.590 --> 00:12:25.670 align:middle line:84%
And that really comes down to
the ingenuity of the Sumerians,

00:12:25.670 --> 00:12:27.830 align:middle line:84%
Akkadians, and
Babylonians who realized

00:12:27.830 --> 00:12:31.370 align:middle line:84%
that cuneiform, etching
into stone or clay

00:12:31.370 --> 00:12:33.218 align:middle line:84%
and then baking that
clay into tablets,

00:12:33.218 --> 00:12:34.760 align:middle line:84%
was the only way
that something could

00:12:34.760 --> 00:12:36.650 align:middle line:90%
survive more than 1,000 years.

00:12:36.650 --> 00:12:39.620 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's why,
because the Egyptians relied

00:12:39.620 --> 00:12:44.632 align:middle line:84%
so heavily on papyrus and paper
records and some hieroglyphs.

00:12:44.632 --> 00:12:46.340 align:middle line:84%
Although, I think
hieroglyphs were mainly

00:12:46.340 --> 00:12:48.600 align:middle line:84%
done by the later
dynastic pharaohs.

00:12:48.600 --> 00:12:49.400 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: Right.

00:12:49.400 --> 00:12:50.120 align:middle line:84%
>>LACROIX: And I
think that's one

00:12:50.120 --> 00:12:52.490 align:middle line:84%
of the reasons why some of
that information has been lost.

00:12:52.490 --> 00:12:54.440 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: And don't forget
the Dead Sea Scrolls.

00:12:54.440 --> 00:12:55.340 align:middle line:84%
>>LACROIX: That's
right, and that's--

00:12:55.340 --> 00:12:56.570 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: Clay tablets, right?

00:12:56.570 --> 00:12:57.737 align:middle line:90%
>>LACROIX: But that's paper.

00:12:57.737 --> 00:12:59.090 align:middle line:90%
The Dead Sea Scrolls is paper.

00:12:59.090 --> 00:13:01.850 align:middle line:84%
And thankfully, it
was put in these caves

00:13:01.850 --> 00:13:04.770 align:middle line:84%
above the Dead Sea, which
was a very, very dry climate.

00:13:04.770 --> 00:13:06.440 align:middle line:84%
So it enables
something like that

00:13:06.440 --> 00:13:09.440 align:middle line:84%
to survive longer than
perhaps other places.

00:13:09.440 --> 00:13:11.150 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: How far
back do you go?

00:13:11.150 --> 00:13:15.200 align:middle line:84%
>>LACROIX: Well, if we were to
look at things like the Brosius

00:13:15.200 --> 00:13:16.940 align:middle line:84%
King List that
came out of Babylon

00:13:16.940 --> 00:13:19.670 align:middle line:84%
and then compare it with the
Uruk List of Kings and Sages

00:13:19.670 --> 00:13:22.850 align:middle line:84%
and the Sumerian King List,
if we take those three

00:13:22.850 --> 00:13:26.960 align:middle line:84%
and we try to combine them
with the ancient pyramid king

00:13:26.960 --> 00:13:29.690 align:middle line:84%
list that came out
of the Giza Plateau,

00:13:29.690 --> 00:13:33.110 align:middle line:84%
we get dates that bring us
well over 50,000 years old.

00:13:33.110 --> 00:13:35.360 align:middle line:84%
Some of them really
point us to something

00:13:35.360 --> 00:13:38.150 align:middle line:84%
more like 200,000 years
old, which is totally

00:13:38.150 --> 00:13:39.685 align:middle line:90%
beyond our comprehension today.

00:13:39.685 --> 00:13:40.520 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: That is amazing.

00:13:40.520 --> 00:13:41.720 align:middle line:84%
>>LACROIX: But it
really shows us

00:13:41.720 --> 00:13:43.910 align:middle line:84%
that, if we were to look
at our civilization that

00:13:43.910 --> 00:13:47.000 align:middle line:84%
has risen largely just
within 1,000 years,

00:13:47.000 --> 00:13:49.130 align:middle line:84%
if you really look at it,
over the course of all

00:13:49.130 --> 00:13:51.230 align:middle line:84%
the technological
advancements and things

00:13:51.230 --> 00:13:53.990 align:middle line:84%
that have happened since the
Middle Ages and everything,

00:13:53.990 --> 00:13:57.740 align:middle line:84%
really, if we look at something
that's over 100,000 years old,

00:13:57.740 --> 00:14:01.550 align:middle line:84%
it almost is beyond our
capability to understand.

00:14:01.550 --> 00:14:04.440 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: And this
history has been lost.

00:14:04.440 --> 00:14:05.510 align:middle line:90%
How do we find it?

00:14:05.510 --> 00:14:08.413 align:middle line:84%
How do you find it with
"Ancient Civilizations?"

00:14:08.413 --> 00:14:09.830 align:middle line:84%
>>LACROIX: The
first thing we have

00:14:09.830 --> 00:14:14.120 align:middle line:84%
to do is we have to shed this
preconditioned notion we get

00:14:14.120 --> 00:14:16.520 align:middle line:84%
from doctrines we're
taught in school, this idea

00:14:16.520 --> 00:14:20.150 align:middle line:84%
that civilization is only
come from a 6,000 year window

00:14:20.150 --> 00:14:23.120 align:middle line:84%
and that everything before
was nomadic hunter gatherers

00:14:23.120 --> 00:14:23.990 align:middle line:90%
and was primitive.

00:14:23.990 --> 00:14:27.110 align:middle line:84%
We need to totally take that
and throw it out and start over

00:14:27.110 --> 00:14:29.870 align:middle line:84%
again and actually look at what
the evidence around the world

00:14:29.870 --> 00:14:30.890 align:middle line:90%
is telling us.

00:14:30.890 --> 00:14:32.840 align:middle line:84%
And what that evidence
from, whether or not

00:14:32.840 --> 00:14:35.000 align:middle line:84%
it's looking at the
ancient Maya or down

00:14:35.000 --> 00:14:37.430 align:middle line:84%
into the pre-Inca,
the Egyptians,

00:14:37.430 --> 00:14:40.550 align:middle line:84%
the Sumerians, the
ancient Japanese,

00:14:40.550 --> 00:14:42.770 align:middle line:84%
or throughout
Southeast Asia, what

00:14:42.770 --> 00:14:45.570 align:middle line:84%
we're seeing from all these
civilizations is they say,

00:14:45.570 --> 00:14:47.300 align:middle line:84%
look, there was a
civilization that

00:14:47.300 --> 00:14:51.080 align:middle line:84%
came long before us that taught
us everything we know now.

00:14:51.080 --> 00:14:53.330 align:middle line:84%
And that civilization
disappeared.

00:14:53.330 --> 00:14:56.060 align:middle line:84%
And that goes so much
further back than we're told.

00:14:56.060 --> 00:14:58.040 align:middle line:84%
So if we take
megalithic evidence

00:14:58.040 --> 00:15:00.200 align:middle line:84%
and look at radiocarbon
dating that we're doing

00:15:00.200 --> 00:15:02.750 align:middle line:84%
and we look at the
totality of all of this,

00:15:02.750 --> 00:15:05.870 align:middle line:84%
we can put together a
timeline and understanding

00:15:05.870 --> 00:15:08.510 align:middle line:84%
to be able to recreate a show
like "Ancient Civilizations"

00:15:08.510 --> 00:15:11.667 align:middle line:84%
that actually tells this
story from the evidence

00:15:11.667 --> 00:15:14.000 align:middle line:84%
rather than just from these
doctrines we've been taught.

00:15:14.000 --> 00:15:17.522 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: Do you touch
on ancient aliens, ETs?

00:15:17.522 --> 00:15:18.980 align:middle line:84%
>>LACROIX: It's
obviously an area--

00:15:18.980 --> 00:15:21.740 align:middle line:84%
if something like that-- if
we have evidence of influences

00:15:21.740 --> 00:15:23.417 align:middle line:84%
that come from the
stars, of course,

00:15:23.417 --> 00:15:24.500 align:middle line:90%
we're going to discuss it.

00:15:24.500 --> 00:15:27.590 align:middle line:84%
But the focus here
is, does the evidence

00:15:27.590 --> 00:15:29.070 align:middle line:90%
support that direction?

00:15:29.070 --> 00:15:31.160 align:middle line:84%
And if it doesn't,
then we don't go there.

00:15:31.160 --> 00:15:33.500 align:middle line:84%
We have to be
open-minded to say what

00:15:33.500 --> 00:15:36.680 align:middle line:84%
is the strongest evidence
telling us from what this says?

00:15:36.680 --> 00:15:40.220 align:middle line:84%
So it's an open-minded show,
but it's largely evidence-driven

00:15:40.220 --> 00:15:41.660 align:middle line:90%
as much as it possibly can be.

00:15:41.660 --> 00:15:43.493 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: You had
mentioned the Great Flood.

00:15:43.493 --> 00:15:46.940 align:middle line:84%
We seem to have stories
abound about that.

00:15:46.940 --> 00:15:50.210 align:middle line:84%
I happen to think maybe an
asteroid hit the planet right

00:15:50.210 --> 00:15:53.060 align:middle line:84%
