to Graham Hancock and Randall

00:16:00.990 --> 00:16:01.790 align:middle line:90%
Carlson--

00:16:01.790 --> 00:16:02.870 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: Great people.

00:16:02.870 --> 00:16:05.282 align:middle line:84%
>>LACROIX: Great researchers,
great people, great minds.

00:16:05.282 --> 00:16:06.740 align:middle line:84%
If we were to look
at that, there's

00:16:06.740 --> 00:16:09.180 align:middle line:84%
really these two camps
that come into play.

00:16:09.180 --> 00:16:11.450 align:middle line:84%
Now, I had a great conversation
with Randall Carlson

00:16:11.450 --> 00:16:13.890 align:middle line:84%
a little while ago where
we were discussing this.

00:16:13.890 --> 00:16:16.370 align:middle line:84%
And he came out and he's, of
course, a trained geologist.

00:16:16.370 --> 00:16:18.150 align:middle line:84%
And he came out
and he was saying,

00:16:18.150 --> 00:16:20.570 align:middle line:90%
look, maybe both are right.

00:16:20.570 --> 00:16:24.560 align:middle line:84%
Maybe what we're looking at is
this Younger Dryas catastrophe

00:16:24.560 --> 00:16:26.780 align:middle line:84%
period, maybe both
things happened.

00:16:26.780 --> 00:16:30.770 align:middle line:84%
And by both I mean we had
impacts from celestial impacts,

00:16:30.770 --> 00:16:31.730 align:middle line:90%
large comets.

00:16:31.730 --> 00:16:34.580 align:middle line:84%
But maybe we also had things
like coronal mass ejections.

00:16:34.580 --> 00:16:36.590 align:middle line:84%
These mini supernovas
from the sun.

00:16:36.590 --> 00:16:38.780 align:middle line:84%
Maybe it all comes
into play because

00:16:38.780 --> 00:16:41.270 align:middle line:84%
of these disruptions to
our outer solar system

00:16:41.270 --> 00:16:42.930 align:middle line:90%
and our star, the sun.

00:16:42.930 --> 00:16:45.920 align:middle line:84%
So really, I think we need to
look at it as maybe the Younger

00:16:45.920 --> 00:16:48.910 align:middle line:84%
Dryas was a combination of all
of these different disastrous

00:16:48.910 --> 00:16:49.710 align:middle line:90%
events.

00:16:49.710 --> 00:16:51.320 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: Let's take a
glimpse of the new season

00:16:51.320 --> 00:16:53.580 align:middle line:84%
