narratives that happened.

00:17:50.930 --> 00:17:53.390 align:middle line:84%
And so in the very
first flood narrative

00:17:53.390 --> 00:17:58.280 align:middle line:84%
it talks about a dark
world or a beginning

00:17:58.280 --> 00:18:00.320 align:middle line:90%
and the end of an age.

00:18:00.320 --> 00:18:04.490 align:middle line:84%
And then there's this cataclysm,
and this flood occurs.

00:18:04.490 --> 00:18:08.090 align:middle line:84%
And the individual
escapes the flood

00:18:08.090 --> 00:18:11.810 align:middle line:84%
with the seven sages,
the seven Abigails.

00:18:11.810 --> 00:18:15.680 align:middle line:84%
And then after that, it is the
beginning of this golden age

00:18:15.680 --> 00:18:19.310 align:middle line:90%
and this new period of time.

00:18:19.310 --> 00:18:24.170 align:middle line:84%
With the Noah flood, there's
civilization that is occurring.

00:18:24.170 --> 00:18:26.690 align:middle line:84%
And the flood
happens because they

00:18:26.690 --> 00:18:29.030 align:middle line:84%
are trying to wipe
out the wickedness

00:18:29.030 --> 00:18:33.110 align:middle line:84%
from on the planet, like you
find in the biblical narrative.

00:18:33.110 --> 00:18:36.530 align:middle line:84%
And Noah survives the
flood, and there's

00:18:36.530 --> 00:18:41.338 align:middle line:84%
no mention of these seven
sages or seven Abigails.

00:18:41.338 --> 00:18:43.130 align:middle line:10%
- So in South America
we have the tradition

00:18:43.130 --> 00:18:46.940 align:middle line:10%
of Viracocha, who is a builder
god that suddenly shows up

00:18:46.940 --> 00:18:50.630 align:middle line:10%
mysteriously after a global
flood wiped everything out.

00:18:50.630 --> 00:18:52.820 align:middle line:10%
And he appears in
specific locations

00:18:52.820 --> 00:18:54.950 align:middle line:10%
with a group of
seven specialists.

00:18:54.950 --> 00:18:58.910 align:middle line:10%
They're experts in their fields
because wherever civilization

00:18:58.910 --> 00:19:01.430 align:middle line:10%
appears on the face of
the Earth after the flood

00:19:01.430 --> 00:19:04.160 align:middle line:10%
and is always one
charismatic leader who

00:19:04.160 --> 00:19:07.280 align:middle line:10%
leads seven crafts people,
experts in their field.

00:19:07.280 --> 00:19:08.530 align:middle line:90%
[END PLAYBACK]

00:19:08.530 --> 00:19:11.440 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: Fascinating,
fascinating indeed.

00:19:11.440 --> 00:19:14.380 align:middle line:84%
And who told Noah
to build that ark?

00:19:14.380 --> 00:19:16.708 align:middle line:84%
>>LACROIX: That story is
one of my favorites of all

00:19:16.708 --> 00:19:18.250 align:middle line:84%
because, really,
what the first thing

00:19:18.250 --> 00:19:20.038 align:middle line:84%
we need to do is
go back and realize

00:19:20.038 --> 00:19:21.580 align:middle line:84%
that the Noah is
actually a term that

00:19:21.580 --> 00:19:23.290 align:middle line:90%
was given as a biblical term.

00:19:23.290 --> 00:19:26.170 align:middle line:84%
His real name in the
ancient Sumerian text

00:19:26.170 --> 00:19:30.985 align:middle line:84%
and into, for instance, the
Atra-Hasis, we find out--

00:19:30.985 --> 00:19:32.860 align:middle line:84%
and in the Epic of
Gilgamesh-- we find out he

00:19:32.860 --> 00:19:35.800 align:middle line:84%
had a couple of names in history
that he actually was called by.

00:19:35.800 --> 00:19:40.690 align:middle line:84%
His name was Ut-napishtim,
or his name was Ziusudra.

00:19:40.690 --> 00:19:42.160 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: I like Noah better.

00:19:42.160 --> 00:19:45.520 align:middle line:84%
>>LACROIX: Well, but his
story is really quite amazing

00:19:45.520 --> 00:19:49.870 align:middle line:84%
because he was actually the very
last of these prediluvian kings

00:19:49.870 --> 00:19:51.790 align:middle line:84%
of one of these
original five cities

00:19:51.790 --> 00:19:53.920 align:middle line:90%
of Sumer known as Shuruppak.

00:19:53.920 --> 00:19:57.070 align:middle line:84%
And his father Ubara-tutu
was the last great king

00:19:57.070 --> 00:19:59.880 align:middle line:84%
of that city, and he was going
to take the reins to rule over

00:19:59.880 --> 00:20:00.680 align:middle line:90%
that city.

00:20:00.680 --> 00:20:03.850 align:middle line:84%
He did briefly until this
great catastrophe occurred.

00:20:03.850 --> 00:20:06.130 align:middle line:84%
And he was the one who
recorded, basically,

00:20:06.130 --> 00:20:08.710 align:middle line:84%
mankind's entire
story because he

00:20:08.710 --> 00:20:11.050 align:middle line:84%
had a very special
bloodline that connected

00:20:11.050 --> 00:20:12.610 align:middle line:90%
to some of these ancient kings.

00:20:12.610 --> 00:20:18.070 align:middle line:84%
And he was told, through a
reed bed from his god Enki,

00:20:18.070 --> 00:20:21.130 align:middle line:84%
basically, how to survive
this catastrophe so

00:20:21.130 --> 00:20:23.020 align:middle line:84%
that his offspring
and his bloodlines

00:20:23.020 --> 00:20:25.450 align:middle line:84%
could literally bring
and carry on humanity.

00:20:25.450 --> 00:20:27.550 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: I'm looking
forward to the new season.

00:20:27.550 --> 00:20:28.090 align:middle line:90%
>>LACROIX: Me too.

00:20:28.090 --> 00:20:30.340 align:middle line:84%
I think that it's really
going to help a lot of people

00:20:30.340 --> 00:20:33.490 align:middle line:84%
piece together some of these
aspects of understanding what

00:20:33.490 --> 00:20:37.270 align:middle line:84%
this real story is but really
coming from as much evidence

00:20:37.270 --> 00:20:38.410 align:middle line:90%
as we possibly can.

00:20:38.410 --> 00:20:40.240 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: What is
the Great Anunna?

00:20:40.240 --> 00:20:42.760 align:middle line:84%
>>LACROIX: The Great Anunna
was the original term

00:20:42.760 --> 00:20:46.240 align:middle line:84%
of these celestial beings that
came here that basically taught

00:20:46.240 --> 00:20:49.900 align:middle line:84%
civilization everything because,
when we think of metallurgy

00:20:49.900 --> 00:20:53.260 align:middle line:84%
or animal husbandry or
mathematics or astronomy,

00:20:53.260 --> 00:20:56.050 align:middle line:84%
every single one of those
things came from one

00:20:56.050 --> 00:20:57.640 align:middle line:90%
single point in history.

00:20:57.640 --> 00:21:00.310 align:middle line:84%
The Sumerians claim that
all of that knowledge,

00:21:00.310 --> 00:21:01.990 align:middle line:84%
which is where we
trace it all back to--

00:21:01.990 --> 00:21:02.660 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: Absolutely.

00:21:02.660 --> 00:21:04.180 align:middle line:84%
>>LACROIX: --was
handed down to them

00:21:04.180 --> 00:21:07.390 align:middle line:84%
through what was called kingship
in the knowledge of the gods.

00:21:07.390 --> 00:21:09.970 align:middle line:84%
And their gods, these
celestial gods, not

00:21:09.970 --> 00:21:13.780 align:middle line:84%
the forces of nature,
physical or nonphysical beings

00:21:13.780 --> 00:21:16.390 align:middle line:84%
that literally communicated
and taught them,

00:21:16.390 --> 00:21:17.932 align:middle line:90%
they were called the Anunna.

00:21:17.932 --> 00:21:20.140 align:middle line:84%
It meant from those who are
from heaven came to Earth

00:21:20.140 --> 00:21:22.390 align:middle line:84%
or from beyond
basically came here.

00:21:22.390 --> 00:21:25.030 align:middle line:84%
And they were called the Great
Anunna and later the Anunnaki

00:21:25.030 --> 00:21:27.070 align:middle line:84%
to the Akkadian and
Babylonian cultures.

00:21:27.070 --> 00:21:30.130 align:middle line:84%
But that was their sky
gods that they essentially

00:21:30.130 --> 00:21:33.220 align:middle line:84%
state all of the
knowledge of civilization

00:21:33.220 --> 00:21:36.395 align:middle line:84%
came from, which is why all of a
sudden everything just took off

00:21:36.395 --> 00:21:38.770 align:middle line:84%
and we became something very
different than what we were.

00:21:38.770 --> 00:21:39.978 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: Something exploded.

00:21:39.978 --> 00:21:41.302 align:middle line:90%
>>LACROIX: Something happened.

00:21:41.302 --> 00:21:42.760 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: How do
we know that there

00:21:42.760 --> 00:21:44.830 align:middle line:90%
were lost civilizations, Matt?

00:21:44.830 --> 00:21:46.750 align:middle line:84%
How do we know this
without evidence?

00:21:46.750 --> 00:21:50.650 align:middle line:84%
>>LACROIX: Well, if we were to
look at, say, this 6,000 year

00:21:50.650 --> 00:21:53.165 align:middle line:84%
model that we're taught in
school, this doctrine, right,

00:21:53.165 --> 00:21:54.790 align:middle line:84%
if we were to look
at that for a second

00:21:54.790 --> 00:21:57.940 align:middle line:84%
and try to consider what's known
as the Mohs hardness scale,

00:21:57.940 --> 00:22:00.850 align:middle line:84%
it means that, if you have a
civilization that's identified,

00:22:00.850 --> 00:22:04.120 align:middle line:84%
like we're told, as being
a Bronze Age civilization,

00:22:04.120 --> 00:22:06.820 align:middle line:84%
right, using bronze
and copper tools,

00:22:06.820 --> 00:22:09.760 align:middle line:84%
it means that, according
to the Mohs hardness scale,

00:22:09.760 --> 00:22:12.340 align:middle line:84%
those tools have
a certain hardness

00:22:12.340 --> 00:22:14.350 align:middle line:84%
that they have to
them, which means

00:22:14.350 --> 00:22:17.620 align:middle line:84%
they can't manipulate something
that's harder than they are.

00:22:17.620 --> 00:22:19.490 align:middle line:84%
You simply can't
do anything to it.

00:22:19.490 --> 00:22:22.870 align:middle line:84%
And what we find is, if we
look at the telltale signs

00:22:22.870 --> 00:22:24.550 align:middle line:84%
of these megalithic
civilizations

00:22:24.550 --> 00:22:26.860 align:middle line:84%
around the world, that
means giant stones,

00:22:26.860 --> 00:22:29.290 align:middle line:84%
and we look at how most of
them are composed of quartzite

00:22:29.290 --> 00:22:32.590 align:middle line:84%
and granite, on the Mohs
hardness scale that's a 7

00:22:32.590 --> 00:22:35.530 align:middle line:84%
or an 8, which means it's
too hard to be able to carve,

00:22:35.530 --> 00:22:37.570 align:middle line:84%
meaning that it's from
a civilization that

00:22:37.570 --> 00:22:41.710 align:middle line:84%
had tools and technology that
was far beyond the capability

00:22:41.710 --> 00:22:43.600 align:middle line:90%
these civilizations were taught.

00:22:43.600 --> 00:22:45.910 align:middle line:84%
And that's what
proves that they're

00:22:45.910 --> 00:22:48.940 align:middle line:84%
part of a lost civilization
because their knowledge

00:22:48.940 --> 00:22:51.280 align:middle line:84%
was more and more
lost over time and not

00:22:51.280 --> 00:22:52.500 align:middle line:90%
gained like we're taught.

00:22:52.500 --> 00:22:55.000 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: I can tell you're so
excited about these subjects.

00:22:55.000 --> 00:22:55.660 align:middle line:90%
You really are.

00:22:55.660 --> 00:22:57.070 align:middle line:90%
You're like a little kid again.

00:22:57.070 --> 00:22:58.360 align:middle line:90%
>>LACROIX: I am.

00:22:58.360 --> 00:23:00.190 align:middle line:84%
It's a very exciting
thing to talk about

00:23:00.190 --> 00:23:03.010 align:middle line:84%
because the evidence is
all around the world.

00:23:03.010 --> 00:23:05.020 align:middle line:10%
And when you know
what to look for

00:23:05.020 --> 00:23:07.840 align:middle line:10%
and when you understand the
story from what they tell us,

00:23:07.840 --> 00:23:11.920 align:middle line:10%
it invigorates you to a level
of understanding of reality

00:23:11.920 --> 00:23:15.170 align:middle line:10%
and understanding the history
of who we are to a completely

00:23:15.170 --> 00:23:15.970 align:middle line:10%
different place.

00:23:15.970 --> 00:23:18.490 align:middle line:10%
And all of a sudden, your
world changes, and you

00:23:18.490 --> 00:23:20.740 align:middle line:10%
see that, look, we come
from something that's

00:23:20.740 --> 00:23:22.690 align:middle line:10%
far greater than we were told.

00:23:22.690 --> 00:23:26.320 align:middle line:84%
We come from something that was
like a spark of consciousness,

00:23:26.320 --> 00:23:28.630 align:middle line:84%
and spark of the
gods, that turned us

00:23:28.630 --> 00:23:31.700 align:middle line:84%
into something that was truly
remarkable in the universe.

00:23:31.700 --> 00:23:34.480 align:middle line:84%
And we have since
fallen to such a degree,

00:23:34.480 --> 00:23:36.320 align:middle line:84%
that we've forgotten
who we were.

00:23:36.320 --> 00:23:40.240 align:middle line:84%
And we have total amnesia of
who truly came through before us

00:23:40.240 --> 00:23:41.470 align:middle line:90%
and who we were.

00:23:41.470 --> 00:23:43.667 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: Egypt and Atlantis,
is there a connection?

00:23:43.667 --> 00:23:44.500 align:middle line:90%
>>LACROIX: There is.

00:23:44.500 --> 00:23:46.333 align:middle line:84%
There's actually some
phenomenal connections

00:23:46.333 --> 00:23:47.560 align:middle line:90%
that people don't know of.

00:23:47.560 --> 00:23:49.960 align:middle line:84%
And when you think
about the story of Plato

00:23:49.960 --> 00:23:52.728 align:middle line:84%
and how he came up with
the Timaeus et Critias.

00:23:52.728 --> 00:23:54.520 align:middle line:84%
A lot of people say
that it was an allegory

00:23:54.520 --> 00:23:55.750 align:middle line:90%
for the perfect civilization.

00:23:55.750 --> 00:23:57.520 align:middle line:84%
But it wasn't based
on anything real.

00:23:57.520 --> 00:24:00.160 align:middle line:84%
But if you actually look
at the evidence from that,

00:24:00.160 --> 00:24:03.970 align:middle line:84%
you find out that Plato learned
about the story of Atlantis

00:24:03.970 --> 00:24:07.490 align:middle line:84%
from Solon and these
temple priests of Egypt.

00:24:07.490 --> 00:24:08.290 align:middle line:90%
See?

00:24:08.290 --> 00:24:11.200 align:middle line:84%
This is where the two connect
because Solon traveled

00:24:11.200 --> 00:24:13.990 align:middle line:84%
to Egypt, and he met
these temple priests

00:24:13.990 --> 00:24:16.000 align:middle line:84%
of a temple that
used to exist called

00:24:16.000 --> 00:24:17.950 align:middle line:90%
Sais, the Temple of Sais.

00:24:17.950 --> 00:24:18.760 align:middle line:90%
And they state--

00:24:18.760 --> 00:24:20.468 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: What do you
mean used to exist?

00:24:20.468 --> 00:24:23.510 align:middle line:84%
>>LACROIX: It was destroyed
about 1,000 years later,

00:24:23.510 --> 00:24:26.575 align:middle line:84%
and all the records that
were there were lost.

00:24:26.575 --> 00:24:27.700 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: Who destroyed it?

00:24:27.700 --> 00:24:29.075 align:middle line:84%
>>LACROIX: We
don't actually know

00:24:29.075 --> 00:24:31.450 align:middle line:84%
because those records of
what happened to that temple

00:24:31.450 --> 00:24:32.900 align:middle line:90%
disappeared to history.

00:24:32.900 --> 00:24:34.960 align:middle line:84%
But what the temple
priests have say state

00:24:34.960 --> 00:24:36.880 align:middle line:84%
is that they were
the ones who had

00:24:36.880 --> 00:24:40.630 align:middle line:84%
recorded the history and
information of Atlantis before.

00:24:40.630 --> 00:24:44.295 align:middle line:84%
And they tell Solon that
you remember one disaster,

00:24:44.295 --> 00:24:46.420 align:middle line:84%
but there have been many
that have come before you.

00:24:46.420 --> 00:24:48.190 align:middle line:84%
And they go into
detail about Atlantis,

00:24:48.190 --> 00:24:50.020 align:middle line:84%
and they state that
they're the ones that

00:24:50.020 --> 00:24:52.360 align:middle line:84%
had the knowledge
contained in the temple

00:24:52.360 --> 00:24:53.380 align:middle line:90%
and within the priests.

00:24:53.380 --> 00:24:55.360 align:middle line:84%
And when it died
with them, it only

00:24:55.360 --> 00:24:59.087 align:middle line:84%
survived with Plato,
Solon, and Diodorus.

00:24:59.087 --> 00:25:00.670 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: Matt, why
is it so important

00:25:00.670 --> 00:25:03.443 align:middle line:90%
for us to understand the past?

00:25:03.443 --> 00:25:05.860 align:middle line:84%
>>LACROIX: Understanding the
past, there's a famous quote.

00:25:05.860 --> 00:25:07.277 align:middle line:84%
"You can't understand
where you're

00:25:07.277 --> 00:25:09.800 align:middle line:84%
going unless you know
where you've come from."

00:25:09.800 --> 00:25:13.870 align:middle line:84%
And so we have to look back to
understand how far we reached,

00:25:13.870 --> 00:25:16.570 align:middle line:84%
the level we were to
have achieved consciously

00:25:16.570 --> 00:25:19.000 align:middle line:84%
and energetically and
realize that we've fallen.

00:25:19.000 --> 00:25:21.550 align:middle line:84%
And if we can't
understand where we were,

00:25:21.550 --> 00:25:24.070 align:middle line:84%
then we're not going to know
how to get back to that again.

00:25:24.070 --> 00:25:26.590 align:middle line:84%
And that place that
we were once at

00:25:26.590 --> 00:25:29.590 align:middle line:84%
tells this incredible
story of civilizations

00:25:29.590 --> 00:25:31.660 align:middle line:84%
that rose up to this
level of understanding

00:25:31.660 --> 00:25:34.270 align:middle line:84%
the universe, the Earth,
harmonics and energy

00:25:34.270 --> 00:25:37.630 align:middle line:84%
and consciousness to a way
where they literally became gods

00:25:37.630 --> 00:25:39.220 align:middle line:90%
like those that created them.

00:25:39.220 --> 00:25:41.890 align:middle line:84%
And we have fallen so
far that we're simply

00:25:41.890 --> 00:25:43.480 align:middle line:84%
trying to put these
pieces together,

00:25:43.480 --> 00:25:45.820 align:middle line:84%
and that's why that
story matters so much.

00:25:45.820 --> 00:25:48.710 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: Did we ever
find ancient maps?

00:25:48.710 --> 00:25:49.510 align:middle line:90%
>>LACROIX: We have.

00:25:49.510 --> 00:25:51.250 align:middle line:84%
Actually, one of
my favorite maps

00:25:51.250 --> 00:25:53.590 align:middle line:84%
that we uncovered when
we were researching

00:25:53.590 --> 00:25:56.140 align:middle line:84%
season 5 of "Ancient
Civilizations"

00:25:56.140 --> 00:26:00.310 align:middle line:84%
is that, in 1907, there
was a map found in Tibet.

00:26:00.310 --> 00:26:02.260 align:middle line:84%
And of course, of all
places like Tibet,

00:26:02.260 --> 00:26:03.370 align:middle line:90%
it makes sense though.

00:26:03.370 --> 00:26:05.197 align:middle line:84%
If there were
global catastrophes,

00:26:05.197 --> 00:26:07.030 align:middle line:84%
you'd want to protect
some of that knowledge

00:26:07.030 --> 00:26:09.460 align:middle line:84%
in one of the highest
areas of the world, right?

00:26:09.460 --> 00:26:12.040 align:middle line:84%
And so in the story that
it's really fascinating

00:26:12.040 --> 00:26:14.620 align:middle line:84%
that's going to go into
season 5 is that we're

00:26:14.620 --> 00:26:18.460 align:middle line:84%
looking at these ancient
Tibetan civilizations, right,

00:26:18.460 --> 00:26:20.950 align:middle line:84%
that go far back,
where they describe

00:26:20.950 --> 00:26:26.350 align:middle line:84%
how the story is that there was
a monk in Tibet who was just

00:26:26.350 --> 00:26:29.770 align:middle line:84%
traveling through the mountains
one day in the early 1900s.

00:26:29.770 --> 00:26:33.520 align:middle line:84%
And he found a cave far
up on this mountainside

00:26:33.520 --> 00:26:36.180 align:middle line:84%
that had been
essentially lost to time.

00:26:36.180 --> 00:26:38.020 align:middle line:84%
He went in this cave,
and what he found

00:26:38.020 --> 00:26:41.270 align:middle line:84%
was a library with records
all over the world, Chinese,

00:26:41.270 --> 00:26:42.070 align:middle line:90%
Sanskrit--

00:26:42.070 --> 00:26:43.462 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: From how far back?

00:26:43.462 --> 00:26:45.295 align:middle line:84%
>>LACROIX: Thousands
and thousands of years.

00:26:45.295 --> 00:26:46.070 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: Oh, my gosh, relics.

00:26:46.070 --> 00:26:48.112 align:middle line:84%
>>LACROIX: And so what
happened was he went back,

00:26:48.112 --> 00:26:51.507 align:middle line:84%
and he ended up telling the
story to an ancient researcher

00:26:51.507 --> 00:26:53.590 align:middle line:84%
