00:36:35.890 --> 00:36:37.720 align:middle line:10%
- There are common
themes that run

00:36:37.720 --> 00:36:39.880 align:middle line:10%
through all of these stories.

00:36:39.880 --> 00:36:42.940 align:middle line:10%
One of those themes
is that civilization

00:36:42.940 --> 00:36:45.880 align:middle line:10%
is cyclic rather than
linear, that there

00:36:45.880 --> 00:36:50.440 align:middle line:10%
have been previous cycles of
civilization that have lasted

00:36:50.440 --> 00:36:52.960 align:middle line:10%
for approximately 5,000 years.

00:36:52.960 --> 00:36:54.130 align:middle line:90%
Something happens.

00:36:54.130 --> 00:36:57.260 align:middle line:84%
Those cycles come to an
end, a new cycle begins.

00:36:57.260 --> 00:36:59.140 align:middle line:84%
This is where it gets
really interesting

00:36:59.140 --> 00:37:02.260 align:middle line:84%
because, even though
the cycles change,

00:37:02.260 --> 00:37:05.740 align:middle line:84%
there appears to be a
continuity of knowledge,

00:37:05.740 --> 00:37:10.090 align:middle line:84%
a continuity of wisdom when it
comes to the end of one cycle

00:37:10.090 --> 00:37:12.316 align:middle line:90%
and the beginning of the next.

00:37:12.316 --> 00:37:16.850 align:middle line:10%
The Mayans divided one
precession of the equinoxes,

00:37:16.850 --> 00:37:20.380 align:middle line:10%
so 26,000 year
cycle approximately,

00:37:20.380 --> 00:37:25.360 align:middle line:10%
into five 5,125
year-long cycles.

00:37:25.360 --> 00:37:28.990 align:middle line:10%
Each of those cycles,
when they begin,

00:37:28.990 --> 00:37:32.250 align:middle line:10%
something happens to the
civilization during that time.

00:37:32.250 --> 00:37:35.230 align:middle line:84%
And one of the questions
that historians have asked

00:37:35.230 --> 00:37:38.950 align:middle line:84%
is, could there be something
that drives these cycles?

00:37:38.950 --> 00:37:40.750 align:middle line:84%
Is there a cosmological
phenomenon?

00:37:40.750 --> 00:37:42.370 align:middle line:90%
Is there a climactic phenomenon?

00:37:42.370 --> 00:37:44.560 align:middle line:90%
Is there a geologic phenomenon?

00:37:44.560 --> 00:37:47.380 align:middle line:84%
Maybe it's a convergence
of all of these phenomenon.

00:37:47.380 --> 00:37:51.980 align:middle line:84%
Something happens
every 5,125 years.

00:37:51.980 --> 00:37:58.300 align:middle line:84%
Well, if we take the year
2012 as the end of one 5,125

00:37:58.300 --> 00:38:04.090 align:middle line:84%
year-long cycle and we go back
in time to the 5,000 years

00:38:04.090 --> 00:38:06.730 align:middle line:84%
previously, this
would be the time

00:38:06.730 --> 00:38:10.210 align:middle line:84%
that we traditionally have
been taught that civilization

00:38:10.210 --> 00:38:12.550 align:middle line:90%
began in 5,500 years ago.

00:38:12.550 --> 00:38:16.450 align:middle line:84%
Now, new discoveries are
revealing the remnants

00:38:16.450 --> 00:38:20.930 align:middle line:84%
of ancient civilizations that
predate that 5,000 years many,

00:38:20.930 --> 00:38:21.730 align:middle line:90%
many times.

